ArrayList:- ArrayList is the Dynamic Array it is Totally Different From Traditional Array it Much More flexible than Traditional Array we can Add or Remove element anytime 
By using ArrayList in ArrayList There is No Size Limit.It is found in the java.util package

The important points about the Java ArrayList class are:

Java ArrayList class can contain duplicate elements.

Java ArrayList class maintains insertion order.

Java ArrayList class is non synchronized.

Java ArrayList allows random access because the array works on an index basis.

In ArrayList, manipulation is a little bit slower than the LinkedList in Java because a lot of shifting needs to occur if any element is removed from the array list.

Syntax:-
ArrayList<Integer> al = new ArrayList<Integer>(); 

ArrayList Methods:-

add(int index, Object element)
addAll(Collection C)
clear()
clone()
indexOf(Object O)
isEmpty?()
remove?(int index)

